    &lt;Title&gt;Dreadful!!! &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Waited over 4 hours with my elderly diabetic mother for a routine outpatients appointment. Nowhere to get a hot drink or a snack without  a long walk back to the shop at the entrance to the hospital. Thank goodness for the compassion of one nurse who eventually after the 4 hour delay brought her a hot drink. It is not unusual to have a long wait in this clinic, usually we are there for 2-3 hours. Totally unsatisfactory. There are a lot of elderly people attending this clinic and they are reluctant to complain. One lady was there from 9am as she came on the patient transport service, she was eventually seen at 13.20 and then had a further wait for the return trip home on the patient transport. This is not good for elderly patients. This is also not good for the staff who were clearly trying their best but were tired and stressed. I suggest you visit this area and address the issues as a matter of urgency. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
